13. Non-Functional Requirements Documentation - Document NFR-01 through NFR-04
Non-functional requirements define the quality attributes, performance standards, and operational constraints of the Cybersecurity Incident Reporting & Response System.
NFR-01: Performance
Description:
The system shall provide timely responses to user actions such as incident reporting, severity classification, and status updates to support rapid incident handling.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	Incident submission response time ≤ 2 seconds
•	Severity classification occurs immediately after submission
•	Dashboard and status updates occur in near real time

NFR-02: Security
Description:
The system shall ensure secure access, data confidentiality, and protection against unauthorized usage.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	Role-based authentication for reporters, SOC analysts, and administrators
•	Unauthorized access attempts are blocked and logged
•	Incident data is accessible only to authorized users

NFR-03: Reliability & Availability
Description:
The system shall be reliable and available to support continuous incident monitoring and response operations.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	System availability of at least 99%
•	No loss of incident data during system failures
•	Automatic recovery from minor system errors

NFR-04: Usability
Description:
The system shall be user-friendly to ensure efficient usage by both non-technical employees and technical security teams.
Acceptance Criteria:
•	Simple and intuitive interface for incident reporting
•	Clear dashboards and workflows for SOC analysts
•	Minimal training required for effective system usage
